# Storyline, Backstory and Character Stats

Title: Encantadia: Echoes of the Gem
Team Name: UXérs

Storyline:
Encantadia was once saved by four legendary Sang’gres.
When darkness kidnapped their Queen and threatened the Brilyantes, Amihan, Alena, Danaya, and Perina rose as protectors of their elements. Through sacrifice and unity, they restored balance to Lireo, Sapiro, Adamya, and Hathoria. Peace returned. But peace, like power, is never permanent. Years after the era of the Four, the Brilyantes began to change. They no longer weakened. They evolved. The elemental gems started resonating beyond royal blood, reacting to emotions across the realms—rage, grief, ambition, fear. The power once bound to queens now answered to something deeper: imbalance within Encantadia itself. Then the unthinkable occurred. The Goddesses Jelian and Joygen vanished. Without divine oversight, the Brilyantes destabilized. Elemental energy clashed violently across the kingdoms. Storms tore through Lireo. Tides swallowed parts of Sapiro. Adamya’s lands cracked open. Flames in Hathoria burned without control.
Ancient guardians Dirk and Mary uncovered a forbidden truth:
A hidden dimension had formed from centuries of accumulated elemental strain—the Gem Void. A realm not created by enemies… but by the Brilyantes themselves. And within it, Jelian and Joygen were sealed—trapped by corrupted resonance. This time, the Brilyantes did not call upon the Sang’gres. They chose new bearers.
Warriors from different paths.
Not queens.
Not heirs.
But individuals whose sacrifices aligned with their element’s core.
Flamara’s unyielding blaze.
Dea’s relentless winds.
Tera’s enduring strength.
Adamus’ disciplined tides.
Tyrone’s burning resolve.
Claire’s flowing precision.
Makelan’s dangerous fury.
The age of royal guardianship had ended.
This is the age of chosen resonance. As the eight rise, they do not replace the Sang’gres—they stand on their legacy. Statues of the Four still tower in the capitals. Songs of their battles echo in ceremonial halls. Their story remains sacred. But the new warriors face a different enemy. Not a rival. Not a kidnapper. But imbalance born from power itself. To save the Goddesses and prevent the Brilyantes from tearing Encantadia apart, they must enter the Gem Void—where elemental energy mutates, memories distort, and even legends can be corrupted.
Because if the Void expands… Encantadia will not fall to darkness. It will collapse under the weight of its own magic.
